caption: I love this spot! They have sensational meals, they have a rich menu, The chef in that spot is very experienced, I enjoy a lot tasting all their food. The food is consistently of high qualtity, the attitude towards the customers  is nice. I often go to  this place and I was never unhappy. I recommend it to all.
they always rush you here and the foods is mediocre
The waitress was so rude and the food (green curry) was not so authentic. Not recommended at all. Many better Thai restaurant out there
One of my fav places for quality Thai food. I can say this place does it for me. Quick and friendly service. Ambience reminds me of San Diego's scene.
thai food and the scene at this place is excellent. I love this place, excellent food & service. This place has a cool feel to it. Mood here is similar to Fresno's scene.
Fantastic Thai food; no frills, just great tastes across the board! 👍

I love their vegetarian pad kee mao. Great service, especially on Saturdays, when they tend to be less crowded. Very nice staff, they make a real effort to remember their customers. Very fast service.
Wonderful Thai restaurant. Great flavours that don't overpower and wonderful service.  I had the Thai Green Curry.
Pad Kee Mao is delicious!
It says Thai food but the people who run the place seemed kind of Chinese to me.
Delicious food. Quick service and nice people.
Good food right across the street, I am lucky.

Probably the grossest pad thai I've ever tried. Ever. I should have picked any other place on google maps... I'm literally writing this after tossing my still warm meal in the trash and headed out to grab anything else for dinner that wasn't that. Dear god.

The restaurant owner and server are total jerks! I walked in with my service dog to pick up my reserved MealPal lunch today. I got the nastiest and condescending look from the owner while being told to step outside the restaurant to wait …
Very delicious duck curry that you don't want to miss.

Pad Thai was very sweet with 10 grams of chicken and hardly any vegetables is the worse one I ever had...service was none , you have to ask for chilli or sauces. Price was very expensive considered what you get!
(Translated by Google) Ok Pad Thai. Sad place with reasonable prices.  (Original) Ok Pad Thai. Tråkigt ställe med hyfsade priser.

I was in town staying at the Sir Francis Drake hotel, so this seemed like a reasonable and proximate place to grab a takeout dinner.  I ordered the egg rolls and pork pad thai.  The food was nothing to write home about.  The egg rolls were …

Mediocre food. Their Tom Yum didn't even have a smell tom yum should have. Also, they included tips to our bill for 4 people, despite the menu says tips are included only for 6 people and more. It wasn't clear at first as everything in the check was in Thai. Little trick to get double tips. Beware.

Don’t ever choose this restaurant if you order from MealPal, I click “I pick up the meal”, but the guy there didn’t honor the meal the rejected to give it to me with the worse attitude that I ever experienced.

The Banana in the tailpipe... I specifically asked if the calamari was the octopus tentacle version and was told it was, but what I received was terribly undercooked breaded strips of some sort. I also ordered the mango sticky rice which …
Mango fried rice, and pumpkin curry dish were above avg.
Nice thai
About 10 mins walk from Union Square. Average taste and dining environment.
This is a nice quant street restaurant. If you like to eat alone and introspect (or watch passing traffic and pedestrians), the ambience is perfect.
Consistently great food. Have been here a dozen times and always leave full and happy.

This place consistently has fantastic food. The restaurant itself is tiny so sometimes it can be tough to find room during the lunch rush but if you do get to a table, the service is great. You can easily get takeout and enjoy it somewhere else as well.
Fast friendly service and very tasty Pad se ew
Fast service. The curry fried rice is pretty good with the right amount of spices
Great food at decent price for downtown SF.
Tasty, quick Thai downtown.
Usually no wait. They have a hidden downstairs that can fit most parties.
Good food and ridiculously cramped seating
Picked up my MealPal lunch from Banana House and it was very tasty. I wished less plastic was used with take out in general. The portions were adequate and the curry was very comfort foody....

Decent Thai joint on Kearny located in the FiDi. Fairly busy when i visited around 12:30. Plenty of seating, good spot to grab lunch with a coworker.  I ordered the yellow chicken curry through MealPal, and while the flavor and spice level was on point, the carrots and onions were really underdone and few and far between.
(Translated by Google) Excellent taste Original Thai family operated restaurant.  (Original) Excelente sabor  Original Thai restaurante operado por la familia.

Great food. Fast service. Reasonable prices. And you can normally get a table with little to no wait. Lots of great Thai dishes to choose from, Pumpkin curry being my favorite. In a sea of overpriced SF trendiness, Banana House is an island of sane tastiness.
Great local place for Thai food and fun.
Great food!
Great Thai food.  That's all
(Translated by Google) A nice little restaurant to discover!  (Original) Un petit resto sympa à découvrir!!!
Below average Thai lunch joint. Friendly service.
Ordered food online through EAT 24 and Had to wait 20 mins to pick up my single order.
Great lunch space. Recommend the Prik Khing and Thai iced tea

We ordered an appetizer to go and it took a long time, the couple behind us got their food first, when my friend payed with cash they did not accept her pennies. I ordered pineapple juice and there was a rubber band inside that i noticed halfway through drinking it. However, I was able to replace it and the cashier said sorry.

Great little spot for a quick bite of wonderful Thai food. The prices are very reasonable and they have a great selection of items. I'm also impressed with how fast they can be with your order. Last but not least, I love how friendly and welcoming they are.

I ordered takeout but once I got to the restaurant I wanted to sit down and eat. They would not serve me and refused to let me sit down. The restaurant was practically empty. They treated me very poorly.
Good food for good price
Delicious thai food with variety of  nice ingredients, is a smaller restaurant and has good dessert options
I had a good green curry chicken there, quickly served and for a very decent price. I recommend this place!
Was OK. The place looks better since the front update.
Very good value eating. We really enjoyed the spice. BYOB
Solid choice for Thai in the Financial District.
Good food at reasonable prices.

The place was not clean and tidy. And the water didn't look like it was safe to drink. No, seriously don't drink it. But the food. Specifically the in-house Banana House duck noodles was perfection. Cannot really put it in words, it was sooo good.
Get the fried bananas with honey. They don't always have it.
Not very good
Good Thai spot when you're in a jam in the FiDi. I come back here for their fresh mango curry.

I really did not enjoy my meal here. I ordered a curry dish with rice.  The curry looked like a bowl full of grease - extremely greasy and I drank bottles of water after because my thirst was unquenchable.  I love Thai food normally but do NOT recommend eating here.
Wasn't good... Disappointed...
Good thai food and very affordable too..
The food was bland and the place wasn't very clean.
Having lived in Thailand I can say this place is very authentic. It's not the westernized Thai food all the complainers are used to.
Prik king is excellent
The food was wonderful! I enjoyed every dish I ordered. This is the place to go if you want good Thai food in San Francisco.
Great Pad see ew, portion sizes are a little too small though
Excellent. Big, chunky fresh veggies in Tom Kha soup. Fresh mango curry. Wonderful.
Simple moderately priced Thai. Get anything with pineapple or squash in it and you will not be disappointed.
Good food for a quick lunch

Made a reservation here but didn't get to order until 20 - 30 minutes after we arrived. The food was really so-so, and with the poor service I probably won't ever come here again. They did bring out something special for the birthday person though, after we asked, so there is that.
